docs.abstract: The Senate, in a rare show of bipartisanship, voted 67 to 31 to ease some financial rules imposed after the 2008 financial crisis.
docs.snippet: The Senate, in a rare show of bipartisanship, voted 67 to 31 to ease some financial rules imposed after the 2008 financial crisis.
docs.lead_paragraph: A decade after the federal government rescued the first of many faltering financial firms, the Senate voted on Wednesday to pass legislation that would relax restrictions on large parts of the banking industry, representing the most significant changes to the rules that were put in place after the 2008 financial crisis.

headline.main: Senate Passes Bill Loosening Banking Rules, but Hurdles Remain in the House
headline.print_headline: Senate Passes a Bill Loosening Banking Rules, but Hurdles Remain in the House

keywords.name: subject
keywords.value: Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act (2010)

docs.abstract: Sri Lanka blocked access to the social network to help stem mob violence directed at its Muslim minority. Facebook said it was cooperating with the government.
docs.snippet: Sri Lanka blocked access to the social network to help stem mob violence directed at its Muslim minority. Facebook said it was cooperating with the government.
docs.lead_paragraph: MUMBAI — In many countries, Facebook is contending with a darkening reputation as a vehicle for  disinformation and false news. The most recent example: Sri Lanka.

headline.main: In Sri Lanka, Facebook Contends With Shutdown After Mob Violence
headline.print_headline: Sri Lanka Blocks Facebook in Effort to Stem Violence

byline.original: By Vindu Goel, Hari Kumar and Sheera Frenkel

docs.abstract: With Ramadan, the holiest month in Islam, on the way, many Muslims see the items as a welcome addition to their festivities.
docs.snippet: With Ramadan, the holiest month in Islam, on the way, many Muslims see the items as a welcome addition to their festivities.
docs.lead_paragraph: For the first time, a major American retailer is offering a dedicated line of decorations for the holiest month on the Islamic calendar: Ramadan, which culminates in the Eid al-Fitr celebration.

headline.main: Party City Offers Ramadan Decorations, a First for a Big U.S. Retailer

docs.abstract: Edward Lampert made the unusual move of offering to have his hedge fund buy parts of Sears, including its Kenmore brand, as it struggles to pay down debt.
docs.snippet: Edward Lampert made the unusual move of offering to have his hedge fund buy parts of Sears, including its Kenmore brand, as it struggles to pay down debt.
docs.lead_paragraph: The chief executive of Sears is its largest shareholder and a major lender to the company. Now, he wants to be its savior, after the retailer tried — unsuccessfully — to find buyers for some of its more valuable brands.

headline.main: Sears C.E.O. Seeks to Buy the Retailer’s More Valuable Parts
headline.print_headline: Who’ll Buy Sears Assets? Sears Chief Raises Hand

docs.abstract: The government said foreign-owned, single-brand retailers would get more time to meet its requirements to sell products made by Indians.
docs.snippet: The government said foreign-owned, single-brand retailers would get more time to meet its requirements to sell products made by Indians.
docs.lead_paragraph: MUMBAI, India — India’s central government moved on Wednesday to reinvigorate its sluggish economy by relaxing rules governing foreign investment in industries including retailing and air travel.

headline.main: India Extends Hand to Apple and Others by Easing Rules on Foreign Firms
headline.print_headline: India Eases Investment Rules, Aiding Apple and Other Foreign Retailers
